ISLAMABAD, Oct 21 (APP): President Dr. Arif Alvi on Friday congratulated the people of Pakistan for coming out of the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) grey list after four years of hard work by government, institutions and individuals.
“Credit to all those who worked tirelessly, made changes in our laws & implemented the will to fight illegal movement of money,” the President said in a tweet posted on his social media account.
